<span id="freeTextContainer518751548442328038">Bridging the gap proved challenging yet possible and worthwhile. <br/><br/>The gap spans between the worldviews of a 21st-century North American middle class woman who lives in a city and a 16th-century Iberian noble woman who lived as a contemplative. <br/><br/>The span was partially bridged. <br/><br/>My earliest church-going memories include attending (illegal) Latin Mass and and contemplating the wall art and icon art which showed its roots in New Spain. <br/><br/>My omnist worldview allowed me to imagine, reach for, and come to u</span>
  <span id="freeText518751548442328038" style="display:none">Bridging the gap proved challenging yet possible and worthwhile. <br /><br />The gap spans between the worldviews of a 21st-century North American middle class woman who lives in a city and a 16th-century Iberian noble woman who lived as a contemplative. <br /><br />The span was partially bridged. <br /><br />My earliest church-going memories include attending (illegal) Latin Mass and and contemplating the wall art and icon art which showed its roots in New Spain. <br /><br />My omnist worldview allowed me to imagine, reach for, and come to understand commonalities. <br /><br />The payoff was exactly what I hoped it would be. I now know what mansion I am on and how I am set to progress to next mansion. I feel encouraged in my inner spiritual work. I now know without a doubt that the hours of prayer, meditation, and some quiet contemplation while on the yoga mat, in front of my altar, on long bus rides, during long waits at doctor offices are enough to help me get off of this mortal coil with all the Grace needed.<br /><br />I am comforted by the writing of a woman far different from me and I from her.</span>
  <a data-text-id="518751548442328038" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
